  All 5 mission write commands (create, result, reflect, advance, close) exit 0 
  with zero stdout on success. No mission ID echoed after create, no "OK" after
  submit. A user running ethos mission create -f foo.yaml has to follow up with
  list to learn the mission ID ‚ÄĒ friction for automation and CLI pipelines. This
   is a CLI design defect worth a bead; minimal fix is echoing the mission ID
  (and maybe the operation) on success. I'll file mission: write commands should
   echo operation outcome on success as P3.

